Yes, you can extend the web chat by using the web chat API or the Watson Assistant web chat toolkit on GitHub. Here are some common tasks you might want to perform:

* Setting and passing context variable values
* Adding user identity information (if you don't enable security)

For example, if you want to set and pass context variable values, you can use the following script:

<script>
function preSendhandler(event) {
event.data.context.skills['main skill'].user\_defined.ismember = true;
}
window.watsonAssistantChatOptions = {
integrationID: "YOUR\_INTEGRATION\_ID",
...
</script>

This script preserves the context of the conversation and adds an $ismember context variable, setting it to true. You can edit the script to set the context variable value as per your requirement.

